# Media Production Naming Conventions

Always follow these conventions when creating, renaming, or referencing media project files and folders.

## Project Folder

Pattern: `YYYYMMDD_[topic-slug]/`

```
20260301_building-data-governance/
```

- Date is the **planned publish date**, not the creation date
- Topic slug: lowercase, words separated by hyphens, no spaces or underscores

## Project Sub-folders

Every project folder must contain exactly these sub-folders:

```
YYYYMMDD_[topic-slug]/
├── aroll/               ← talking head / camera footage
├── screen/              ← screen recordings
├── assets/
│   ├── canva-exports/   ← exported graphics from Canva
│   └── reference/       ← reference images, inspiration, brand assets
├── export/              ← final rendered output files
└── _COWORK_INSTRUCTIONS.md
```

## Export Files

| Asset | Pattern | Example |
|-------|---------|---------|
| Final video | `YYYYMMDD_[topic-slug]_v1.mp4` | `20260301_building-data-governance_v1.mp4` |
| Camtasia project | `YYYYMMDD_[topic-slug]_v1.tscproj` | `20260301_building-data-governance_v1.tscproj` |
| Thumbnail A | `YYYYMMDD_[topic-slug]_thumb-A.png` | `20260301_building-data-governance_thumb-A.png` |
| Thumbnail B | `YYYYMMDD_[topic-slug]_thumb-B.png` | `20260301_building-data-governance_thumb-B.png` |

- Version suffix (`_v1`, `_v2`) increments on major re-edits
- Thumbnails use `-A` / `-B` for A/B test variants

## Channel Configs

Platform publishing specs live in `/channels/`:

```
channels/
├── youtube.md           ← active v1.0
├── linkedin-video.md    ← planned
└── podcast.md           ← planned
```

One file per distribution channel. Status noted at top of each file.
